definition.value: A hydroxyisoflavone that is isoflavone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7 and methoxy groups at the 2', 4' and 5' positions.
A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is  daidzein substituted by a 6-O-(carboxyacetyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage.
A  glycosyloxyisoflavone that is genistin in which the hydroxy hydrogen at position 6'' has been replaced by a malonyl group.
A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is isoflavone substituted by a methoxy group at position 6, a hydroxy group at position 4' and a  beta-D-glucopyranosyloxy group at position 7.
A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is glycitin substituted by a  malonyl group at position 6''.
A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is  formononetin attached to a 6-O-(carboxyacetyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage.
A methoxyisoflavan that is  (R)-isoflavan substituted by a methoxy group at position 4' and hydroxy groups at positions 7 and 2' respectively.
A pseudobaptigenin that is pseudobaptigenin substituted by a hydroxy groups at position 2'.
A hydroxyisoflavanone that is isoflavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2, 6, 7 and 4' respectively.
A homodetic bicyclic heptapeptide having a sulfide bridge.
A 3beta-hydroxy-Delta(5)-steroid that is campesterol carrying two hydroxy groups at positions 22R and 23R.
A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is (22S)-22-hydroxycampest-4-en-3-one bearing an additional hydroxy substituent at position 23R.
A  germacranolide isolated from Elephantopus mollis and has been shown to exhibit antineoplastic activity.
